items.title: At least 132 killed in Rio police raid, officials say
items.description: The police operation targeting a criminal gang in a densely-populated area of Rio is the deadliest in the city.

items.title: Jamaicans start to reveal devastation as hurricane causes floods, power cuts and splits city in two
items.description: With communication networks in Jamaica crippled, the true scale of the disaster remains unknown.

items.title: Israeli strikes in Gaza kill 104, health ministry says, after Hamas accused of killing soldier
items.description: US President Trump says "nothing" will jeopardise the two-week-old ceasefire despite the flare-up of violence.

items.title: US will reduce its troops on Nato's eastern flank, Romania says
items.description: Bucharest said between 900 and 1,000 American troops would remain stationed in Romania - down from 1,700.

items.title: Sudan's military expels top UN food aid officials as conflict escalates
items.description: Two WFP officials are give 72 hours to leave without explanation - days after a key city falls to the RSF.
